        "body": "## Summary\n- Add Swival as a supported coding agent: new `src/core/agents/swival.ts` adapter (quiet mode, stdin-piped prompt with appended output schema, default `--yolo` permission, buffered JSON parse), wired through `factory.ts` and `config.ts` with accompanying unit tests.\n- Document the new agent in `README.md` and `AGENTS.md`, and extend the bug report template so users can select `swival` and are reminded to include their provider/model.\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n✅ Low: Adds a new agent adapter in a well-isolated, additive way, closely following the existing pi.ts pattern (Windows shell handling, process-tree termination, schema-driven output validation, reserved-arg gating) with comprehensive unit tests; no shared logic was modified.\n\n## Testing\n\n- Summary: Ran the new swival agent tests and the targeted factory/config/cli suites, then the full unit test suite — all 528 tests pass.\n- `npx vitest run src/core/agents/swival.test.ts src/core/agents/factory.test.ts src/core/config.test.ts src/cli.test.ts`\n- `npx vitest run --exclude test/e2e.test.ts`\n- Outcome: ✅ passed across 1 run (45.9s)\n\n## Pipeline\n\nUpdates from [git push no-mistakes](https://github.com/kunchenguid/no-mistakes)\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ **Rebase** - passed</summary>\n\n**Round 1** - passed ✅\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>⚠️ **Review** - 1 info</summary>\n\n**Round 1** - found 1 info\n- ℹ️ `README.md:292` - Grammar typo in user-facing docs: &#34;Swival&#39;s does not stream token usage&#34; should read &#34;Swival does not stream token usage&#34;. The stray apostrophe-s makes the sentence ungrammatical.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ **Test** - passed</summary>\n\n**Round 1** - passed ✅\n- `npx vitest run src/core/agents/swival.test.ts src/core/agents/factory.test.ts src/core/config.test.ts src/cli.test.ts`\n- `npx vitest run --exclude test/e2e.test.ts`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>🔧 **Document** - 3 issues found → auto-fixed</summary>\n\n**Round 1** - found 3 issues (1 warning, 2 infos)\n- ⚠️ `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.yml:62` - The Agent dropdown in the bug report template does not include `swival`. With swival now an officially supported agent, users running it cannot select it when filing a bug; they must fall through to `other / not sure`. Add `swival` to the dropdown options list (between `pi` and `other / not sure`).\n- ℹ️ `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.yml:71` - The &#39;Model / provider&#39; field description says &#39;For opencode, copilot, or pi this is especially useful&#39;. Swival also requires a user-configured provider/model (per its README row and config docs), so it should be added to that list of agents where the model/provider info is especially useful.\n- ℹ️ `README.md:292` - Grammatical error in the Swival row: &#39;Swival&#39;s does not stream token usage, so `--max-tokens` is a no-op.&#39; The possessive `Swival&#39;s` is wrong here - it should read &#39;Swival does not stream token usage, so `--max-tokens` is a no-op.&#39;\n\n**Round 2** (auto-fix) - passed ✅\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ **Lint** - passed</summary>\n\n**Round 1** - passed ✅\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ **Push** - passed</summary>\n\n**Round 1** - passed ✅\n\n</details>\n",
